levelInfo:
Welcome Defense Commander.

In order to be cleared for interplanetary travel, you first need to clear basic training.
Place towers by the path to defend the base from invaders.
Click the map to buy and place a tower.
Keep an eye on health in the top left corner, and gold in the bottom left corner.

Don't forget, the sidebar retracts!
Think about placing towers where they can touch more of the path. For instance, try placing a tower in the corner on this level.

Enemy waves get stronger over time. Don't forget to buy more towers as you accumulate gold!
We're also going to throw a more advanced soldier into the mix so get ready!

Try updating a tower - place the tower, then click the 'upgrade' button on the sidebar!

Sometimes there will be objects in the way. Place towers where you can!

This is a tough one, so we're going to give you a new tower!
The Glider Tower is great for quickly defeating weak enemies.
You also need to be able to defend against fast raiding parties. Make sure to place a lot of towers!

It's time we added a third tower for you to use!

Use the Blinker Tower when you need to deal high amounts of damage as fast as possible.
Make sure you keep an eye on your gold and use it when you can!
This terrain is super rocky, pay attention to tower range!

Here's your final test, Commander.
Complete this and you'll be cleared to serve on other planets around the galaxy.

Good Luck!
Welcome to World 2! Be warned, some of the enemies here are much stronger and take a lot more firepower!
You're gonna need another tower for this one. The fumarole tower is strong and has a great range, but reload time takes awhile.
Enemies are smart - they know the shortest path to your castle.
There's something odd about this map - beware of hidden enemy shortcuts!

Danger! The enemy has disabled most of your towers!

They're sending in heavy forces!
Watch out, there's a big rock formation around the path.

The path here goes around a large rock formation,
but it seems that you can place a tower or two in the center.

The enemy is sending in their light forces,
but we only have these big towers!

Foiled again! The enemy is sending in their heavy forces,
but we only have these light towers!

Rocks have blocked most of the path and our base is in disarray!

Quickly! Place a tower on that center island!
The enemy is unveiling their new unit. Keep your eyes sharp.

This base has been abandoned for a while, so we only
have the block towers.

The alien commander is leading a legion of light forces.

Be sure to mix your towers to handle all enemy types.
Watch out! The alien commanders are coming with their elite troops.

The highway carrying the shipment of glider towers has been
destroyed by rocks. Prepare your defenses before the enemy arrives.

There's a few spots in the middle of the road to place towers.

Get ready before the enemy comes.

The enemy commander is known to double his efforts when he loses.

Prepare for the worst.

The enemy commander doesn't believe in mixed waves.

Be sure to sell your towers to have the optimal defense ready.

How fortunate! The enemy's path has been blocked by a rock!

That said, watch out since there isn't much space to build.

The enemy is attacking our line in the sand again.

Uh oh! It looks like they've brought more troops this time.

We've tracked another distress signal to a new planet.

Be careful, this planet is covered in acid and the aliens seem to suck the life from everything they touch.

They've teamed up with a new type of space criminal and are calling themselves some sort of "Suicidal Squadron".

There's a base camp that's been surviving in this dead jungle for years and has just been discovered.

The aliens have landed amongst a field of hearts and are using it as cover.

We've tracked a newly landed spaceship with a moderately sized army heading towards a base.

Put a stop to this behavior right now.

Watch out for aliens.

The aliens seem to have discovered some fandangled tree camouflage.

Luckily it's only these specific aliens in this specific area so we most likely won't see this again.

Anyways, shoot em with bullets.
You've got a lot of space to work with here but it seems like the enemy is going to try and take advantage of your laziness.

This is going to be tough, the aliens have found a path away from our normal reach.

Scout Recommendations: Rely on upgrades, your godlike ability to stop time, and watch out for acid potholes.

There is a large army heading our way, they've already begun destroying the surrounding wildlife.

We don't have many footholds here so make good use of what you can.

We've pushed the invaders out of most of the territories.

We've discovered a small base located deep in the jungle that needs protecting.

Unfortunately, they have very little space for defenses.

Apparently there are still people living in other places on this acid-filled planet.

They also know we're here to protect them so we can't exactly leave.

This is it.

The final defense.

The've brought together every able-bodied fighter they have left for one final push.

This is for all the marbles.
If you lose here, it'll be like you never defended a single base.

They're coming at you with everything they've got.

Good Luck.
